description: I've prepared a complete Bash script that accomplishes everything you requested. It:  Updates your Omarchy/Arch system with sudo pacman -Syu. Installs jre-openjdk-headless (minimal Java runtime for the server), languagetool (from official repos), and libreoffice-extension-languagetool (from AUR via makepkg -si—no AUR helper assumed). Downloads the latest stable LanguageTool release (v6.6 as of now) via curl, extracts it to ~/.local/share/languagetool. Creates a user-level systemd service (~/.config/systemd/user/languagetool.service) to run the LanguageTool HTTP server on http://localhost:8081 using the local JAR, with auto-restart and CORS enabled for browser extensions. Enables and starts the service immediately, so it auto-starts on login.
